 exploring a wide range of examples from practice. Since the first edition, there has been a perceptible increase in the structured involvement of communities in developing, delivering and evaluating public policies and projects. In this new edition all chapters have been fully updated in the light of recent developments and new case examples have been included to illustrate such changes. A new chapter on The Managers Role in Community Research has been added and a new concluding chapter explores key challenges which need to be addressed. This book is an essential resource for operational and strategic managers in local government, housing, health and other service delivery agencies, social inclusion and community regeneration projects. It will be essential reading for tutors and students on a wide range of undergraduate and Masters courses.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCommunity developmentzGreat Britain. 0aCommunity organizationzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aBanks, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBanks, Sarah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBarr, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButcher, Hugh L, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aButcher, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilchrist, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHawtin, Murray, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerrmann, Tony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMayo, Marjorie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrton, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrton, Andrew, 